summary: this can probably be easily disproved but what if bex and bowie have a courthouse wedding? tbh that seems more realistic for...
body: this can probably be easily disproved but what if bex and bowie have a courthouse wedding? tbh that seems more realistic for them and would be pretty unique for DC. I can imagine them both realizing last minute that they do want to take a chance and get married like…completely out of nowhere like it’s the middle of the school day and they show up at andi’s school practically yelling at the principal to let her out of class and andi goes to the office thinking she’s in trouble for some event related to the episode plot, only to see her parents there (both of them looking the same except bex is maybe wearing a white blouse under a flannel and bowie stuck a bow tie on to his own shirt kjhsjksh) and they’re like “we’re getting married let’s go!!!” and andi’s just like ??? but what about the dress?? the cake?? the invitations??? and bex is like “screw all that let’s GO!!!” and they all run down to the courthouse where cece is waiting for them bc they called her on the way to andi’s school and cece’s the only one dressed up for a wedding bc she WILL wear her nice dress dammit. and then afterwards is the reception where we see everyone together!

summary: Cyrus coming out to his friends and Jonah.. just wow. I cried tears of joy. I wish Andi Mack aired back in 2012 when I came out...
caption: Cyrus coming out to his friends and Jonah.. just wow. I cried tears of joy. I wish Andi Mack aired back in 2012 when I came out as lesbian when I was younger. Never in my life would I’ve thought that disney channel would get so progressive. This show with it’s characters and story reaches many who are in similar situations (disability/teen mom/LGBTQ+/etc.). It’s like having someone sit down with you and telling you it’s gonna be ok. When I have kids, I want to show them this show.
